{"build_type":"library","description":"Reclaim a finished worker's arena block and associated resources after its exit sentinel is observed. Arena blocks, stacks, launch regions, overflow chunks, and child free-list chunks return through the shared reclaim rings when their size class is supported, with the thread-local arena free list retained only as the overflow fallback. Slice 3: also walks the child's g_arena_current_chunk overflow chain (block[5], byte 40) via release-iteration down to the seed block, reclaiming grown-from-pool chunks (no-op under fixed=1 where current_chunk==block). Slice 3: after reclaiming, if the pool is armed and the memory-available doorbell (g_kernel_pool_base+808) has waiters, posts it (announce-readiness-waking-doorbell-waiters) so a caller parked on pool exhaustion re-checks. Slice: the block, stack and launch region are now returned to the SHARED lock-free reclaim ring (return-chunk-toward-reclaiming-structure-local, slab at g_kernel_pool_base+832) on the gone-edge — immediate, event-driven, reusable by any thread and any later reconcile — instead of this thread's private g_arena_free_list (which died with the collector). Ring-FULL or non-class sizes fall back to the thread-local list. Config D: the overflow-chain and child free-list (slot 40/120) are ALSO returned to the shared reclaim ring via return-overflow-chain-to-reclaim (grown chunks reusable cross-thread/cross-reconcile).","module_name":"recycle-worker-arena-block-into-recycled-pool","package_name":"recycle-worker-arena-block-into-recycled-pool","function_definitions":{"recycle-worker-arena-block-into-recycled-pool":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"region","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"block","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variabl